AssetAddressUpdated(string,address,addre.notice: Emitted when an asset address is updated If `previousAddress` was 0, it means that the asset was added to the registry

AssetRangeUpdated(address,(uint256,uint2.notice: Emitted when an asset range is updated

GovernorChangeRequested(address).notice: Emmited when the governor is change is requested

GovernorChanged(address,address).notice: Emmited when the governor is changed

StableAssetAdded(address).notice: Emitted when an asset is set as being stable

StableAssetRemoved(address).notice: Emitted when an asset is unset as being stable

STABLECOIN_IDEAL_PRICE().notice: a stablecoin should be equal to 1 USD

acceptGovernance().notice: Called by the pending governor to approve the change

addStableAsset(address).notice: Adds a stable asset to the registry The asset must already be registered in the registry

changeGovernor(address).notice: Changes the governor can only be called by the current governor

getAssetAddress(string).notice: Returns the address associated with the given asset name e.g. "DAI" -> 0x6B175474E89094C44Da98b954EedeAC495271d0F

returns._0: the price range of the asset

getRegisteredAssetAddresses().notice: Returns a list of addresses for the registered assets

getRegisteredAssetNames().notice: Returns a list of names for the registered assets The asset are encoded as bytes32 (big endian) rather than string

getStableAssets().notice: Returns a list of addresses contaning the stable assets

returns._0: true if the asset address is registered
true if the asset name is registered
true if the asset name is stable

removeStableAsset(address).notice: Removes a stable asset to the registry The asset must already be a stable asset

setAssetRange(address,(uint256,uint256)).notice: Sets the price range (floor and ceiling) for the given asset
